comment._content:
Lieutenant Edwin Francis TRUNDLE - Insurance Broker, 26th Battalion A.I.F. Wounded POZIERES, 1st August 1916. Discharged England 17th August 1919. Post War Non Military Employment with William OWEN and Company, Insurance Assessors, 7 Queen Victoria Street, London.  
Born: Brisbane, Queensland - 4 September 1889 - Died: 1955.

2350 Private Victor Charles TRUNDLE - Bank Clerk, 15th Battalion A.I.F. Discharged medically unfit (asthma) Returned to Australia ex Suez per H.T. “Suffolk” 29 January 1916. 
Born: Brisbane, Queensland - 30 June 1893 - Died: 19th Feb 1940

21429 Sergeant Claude Ernest TRUNDLE - Farmer, 8th Field Artillery Brigade A.I.F. Wounded BASEUL, 23rd Nov 1918. Returned to Australia per H.T. “Ypiringa”, 9th January 1920.
Born: Brisbane, Queensland - 31 March 1891 - Died: 1971
